Over the course of this year, the new vehicle market in South Africa has been under some strain as consumers opt for better value and greater affordability in the second-hand market. This can be attributed to a myriad of economic factors including: raised cost of living, a weakening rand and higher interest rates. As consumersâ€™ budgets shrink, investigating purchasing used cars to stretch every rand becomes more important. When making the new versus used decision, each of us must examine our unique set of financial and life requirements. A little introspection is good for the soul and the wallet. For most people, we think it makes more sense to buy used, but there are some exceptions. In order to make a smarter choice for yourself and your future, you must consider a few factors: Faisal Mkhize, Managing Executive of Absa Vehicle and Asset Finance.